4.87/5  rDev +9.2%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75Poured cold into a tulip glass.  Bottled on 11/12/14, consumed on 12/19/14.
Look = 4.5 Pours a cloudy golden orange color with 2.5 fingers of thick, creamy off white head.  Great retention and lace.
Aroma = 5.0 Hops everywhere!  Citrus and tropical fruit notes are everywhere!  Big orange juice, pineapple, mango - really strong and smells great!
Taste = 5.0 Terrific.  Citrus and tropical fruit flavors dominate, really juicy.  Hop forward with a little sweet malt balance. A moderate bitterness on the finish.
Feel = 4.5 Light feel for a DIPA, not syrupy but also not watery.  Low resin, juicy.  Medium bodied with medium carbonation; fits the flavor profile well.
Drinkability = 4.75 Incredibly drinkable DIPA, low bitterness and terrific flavor profile.  Could sip on all day long.
Overall = 4.825 New highest rated beer for me.  Terrific in all categories. 861 characterskbwalters, Apr 04, 2015
