4.62/5  rDev +3.6%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Purchased today from the source
Poured into FFF Teku
Pour: An inviting deep, deep copper orange with outstanding clarity. Head is a solid two fingers of off white with huge amount of thick lacing left. I just really like the color on this one for some reason.
Smell: Not a surprise but the nose is your typical FFF DIPA but one that I continually enjoy. Citrus with pineapple, mango, grapefruit, tangerine and melon dominate. Then some resinous hop presents and some floral hops. There seems to be a sweet component such as honey to balance everything out. I do not get any alcohol on the smell.
Taste: Again the citrus is the key player and the orange (tangerine), grapefruit, some pineapple and a touch of the mango hits at first. This is followed up by some oily resin like hops that helps create a nice hop bite. Then an almost deep dark like honey sweetness peeks through creating a comforting sweet balance. I would classify this one as a juicy DIPA with a sweet twist. Funny I don't get the 100 IBU's though.
Mouthfeel: Smooth and slick and surprisingly light and easy drinking for a high ABV and IBU. The finish is crisp and refreshing.
Overall: I have come to expect nothing but good from FFF with this style. I have to admit they all taste similar to a degree but holy shit I find this one so flavorful and enjoyable that I believe another drive out to the brewery will be needed before these are gone. This is one that I wish they would add to their regular line up because I'd be one happy man. 1,512 characterssleuthdog, Apr 06, 2013
