4.73/5  rDev +6.1%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75On-tap at Pizzeria Paradiso DuPont Circle, brewed in collaboration with Pig Destroyer for the NHC 2013 conference, unknown brew date, poured into a snifter glass, drank 3/28/13 over ~one hour.
A: 4.75 -bright orange, impressive clarity (considering the aroma), soft vertical bubbles and legs, one finger frothy white head that resolves into subtle glass lacing;
S: 4.75 - lots and lots of tangerine, grapefruit and pine pouring out of the glass; I don't know the hop profile but would anticipate some Citra and Simcoe in the mix 
T: 4.75 - I'm not terribly keen on sweet DIPAs but this one delivered; moderate hop bitterness on the front of the tongue explodes into tropical sweet madness - grapefruit, papaya, mango and blood orange
M: 4.5 - moderate booziness at 9+%, solid carbonation and lingering flavors 
O: 47.5 - I am so glad that I had the opportunity to try some 3Fs beers again as part of CBC 2013, and this beer was a pleasant surprise but, to be honest, I shouldn't have been surprised by its quality; it simultaneously hits hard with hops and sweetness, which, to be frank, is really difficult to pull off well because most sweet "Third Coast" DIPAs are sickingly sweet for my tastes; in sum, this is another fine example from The Hop Lords 1,259 charactersMNishCT77, Mar 28, 2013
4.81/5  rDev +7.8%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75Another amazing new three Floyd's offering at pizzeria paradiso DuPont during CBC week in DC. Man this is awesome, can we hold this every year in DC please? 
The beer pours a very pretty orange fairly clear color with a small ring of head and some nice lacing. 
The smell opens up nicely with some orange rind, tropical fruit, honey, nice semi sweet bitters and slight bit of alcohol warmth that completely mingle with the hops. The flavor is just phenomenal, huge hops right away and all throughout the flavor, grapefruit, tropical fruit, weed, perfect amount of malt and alcohol to compliment it all. Just super resiny, sticky, outstanding. Might be hard to drink a lot of this because of the incredible complexity and thickness of the hop bill. 
An awesome, awesome beer, they again are masters of the hop! I am not worthy. 829 charactersDreadnaught33, Mar 28, 2013
4.63/5  rDev +3.8%look: 4 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5On tap at Pizzeria Paradiso Dupont.
Pours a light straw clear beer. Frothy white head atop the beer which recedes to a white thin ring. Not much to look at but the aroma and flavor makes up for it. 
The aroma is on par with other big DIPAs. Big tangerine peel notes, some pine, and slight onion. Dry cracker malt profile lingers in the background, but barely noticeable.
The flavor is ridiculously big on hops. This might pack the most hop flavor of any beer I've had. Super citrusy tangerine peel. Floral, pine cones, slight onion.
Tongue scorching bitterness. Medium carbonation. 
Overall this is a SERIOUS DIPA. This is unequivocally the most powerful DIPA, flavor-wise, I've had. Crazy good and definitely something to seek out for hopheads. 750 charactersahalloin, Mar 28, 2013
